results.content: Provision of Services to Address the Agricultural Pollution in the Litani River Basin (LRB)

description: The contracting authority intends to implement agricultural interventions in the Litani River Basin (LRB) in order to address the pollution caused by the dominant agricultural practices. The uncontrolled quality and quantities of pesticides, insecticide, herbicides, and fertilisers, and the bad utilisation of animal fertilisers on agriculture lands result in both water and soil pollution. The contract scope consists of disseminating best agricultural practices, introducing alternative irrigation and production techniques (including agro-food processing), and on-the-job and plot-demonstration training modules. Strategies for involving youth in these activities will be devised to preserve the agricultural identity of the region and impact positively on social cohesion. Farmers and cooperatives will be supported to maintain their yields and to identify ways for scaling up and improving their production or reaching new markets.

description: Les travaux prévus dans le cadre du présent marché consistent à faire la réhabilitation et l’entretien des routes et pistes rurales dans les cinq provinces ci-dessus citées. Ces travaux qui dureront trois (3) ans seront exécutés avec l’approche de Gestion et entretien par niveaux de service (GENIS). En effet, la première année sera réservée à la remise à niveau par la réhabilitation des sections/points critiques ainsi que la réparation et la construction des ouvrages hydrauliques. Après la remise à niveau, l’entreprise aura la responsabilité d’assurer le service de l’entretien durant tout le reste de la durée du marché en vue de maintenir le niveau de service. Elle sera notamment chargée de la pose et de la gestion des barrières de pluie.

results.summary: EU-GCC Cooperation on Green Transition and De-carbonisation
results.content: EU-GCC Cooperation on Green Transition and De-carbonisation

description: The Overall Objective of the action is to contribute to stronger political and technical relations between the European Union (EU) and the countries of the Cooperation Council for the Arab States of the Gulf  (GCC) (Bahrain, Kuwait, Oman, Qatar, Saudi Arabia and the United Arab Emirates), at regional and bilateral levels. The Specific Objective of this action is to deepen engagement in the area of climate change and promote the uptake of green transition policies and technologies by the GCC countries. Special focus will be given to exchange of best practices in the sectors of de-carbonisation, green transition and climate change adaptation. The Action will underpin a substantive dialogue on the above topics; will develop customized policy and practice options to support green transition in the GCC Countries and will facilitate an enhanced cooperation on climate change including in the areas of research and business.
title: EU-GCC Cooperation on Green Transition and De-carbonisation

results.summary: Supply of IT Equipment for Enhancing e-Government
results.content: Supply of IT Equipment for Enhancing e-Government

description: The subject of the contract is the supply, delivery, unloading, siting and installation, commissioning, testing and maintenance during warranty period of IT equipment that will host new developed registers and e-services for enhanced public service delivery, and reduce time and costs of citizens and businesses when interacting with public bodies.The system should provide sufficient IT resources for operation of newly developed registers and e-services on main data center, to provide business continuity on the disaster recovery site and should provide secure connectivity of beneficiaries that are still not part of Interoperability platform.

results.summary: Supervision of Works for Infrastructure Improvement of Facilities within the Justice and Penitentiary Sector
results.content: Supervision of Works for Infrastructure Improvement of Facilities within the Justice and Penitentiary Sector

description: Under the project, infrastructure of facilities within the justice and penitentiary sector are addressed. The successful Contractor will provide:(a) the services for the drafting of a works tender dossiers based on EU PRAG templates. The works will include:(i) reconstruction/adaptation of courts for access of persons with reduced mobility/improving energy efficiency of the facilities – 6 buildings in total (2 in Podgorica, 1 in Bijelo Polje, Kotor, Berane and Niksic;(ii) construction of facilities for the Criminal Enforcement Administration in Danilovgrad;(iii) adaptation of the customs facilities/border crossing point at Bar; and(iv) adaptation of the former border post Bozaj.(b) The site supervision services assuming the role of the Supervisor’s Representative for above mentioned works. The supervision will be delivered in accordance with the Montenegrin construction legislation and PRAG conditions for works contract.
title: Supervision of Works for Infrastructure Improvement of Facilities within the Justice and Penitentiary Sector

results.content: Organisation artistique et logistique des Semaines du film européen - 30 & 31e éditions, Maroc

results.summary: Urban Development Technical Facility
results.content: Urban Development Technical Facility

description: This service Contract is designed to support actors managing or implementing EU cooperation programmes at global, regional and country level to assess, design, monitor, implement and evaluate sustainable urban development and planning interventions and to support policy work on this matter. The technical assistance work will be demand driven and will cover all the countries where INTPA is active (requests will come both from EU Delegations and from INTPA HQ).  The contractor will have to deliver high level technical assistance and policy advice at country, regional and global level through expert advice and field missions in order to support committed countries and partners to reach the SDG11 objectives. Given the geographical span and the multidisciplinary topic, it is foreseen that the contractor will mobilise a broad pool of non-key experts to support the Key experts.
title: Urban Development Technical Facility

results.summary: Improving the Quality of Education
results.content: Improving the Quality of Education

description: The aim of the contract is to improve the quality of secondary (general and VET) education by supporting the quality assurance system through investing in teachers’ professional development. It includes two key elements:1) Support of teacher professional development in accordance with the professional standards and competences based on the new Law on teachers and professional associates in primary and secondary schools; and2) Further support in implementation of the newly introduced pedagogical and methodological approaches for inclusive education in accordance with the new concept for inclusive education.

results.summary: Actividades de Comunicación Estratégica de la Cooperación y Diplomacia Pública de la Unión Europea en Guatemala
results.content: Actividades de Comunicación Estratégica de la Cooperación y Diplomacia Pública de la Unión Europea en Guatemala

description: El presente contrato ayudará a la Delegación de la Unión Europea en Guatemala a diseñar, producir, organizar e implementar una serie de actividades y eventos de comunicación y visibilidad para garantizar la implementación de las actividades de comunicación estratégica de la Cooperación y Diplomacia Pública de la Unión Europea en Guatemala por un período de 48 meses. El ámbito de este contrato será la comunicación externa de la Unión Europea en Guatemala ante los diferentes socios visibilizando, en particular, las actividades de cooperación en el marco de las tres prioridades temáticas definidas en el Programa Indicativo Plurianual para Guatemala, las iniciativas emblemáticas del Equipo Europa en Guatemala, las fechas conmemorativas de la UE y de Guatemala, así como los marcos políticos generales entre la Delegación de la Unión Europea y la República de Guatemala.
title: Actividades de Comunicación Estratégica de la Cooperación y Diplomacia Pública de la Unión Europea en Guatemala

results.summary: Construction of: Lot 1- As Samua breed station including laboratory building and supplying and installing surveillance system and Lot 2: Yatta Slaughterhouse
results.content: Construction of: Lot 1- As Samua breed station including laboratory building and supplying and installing surveillance system and Lot 2: Yatta Slaughterhouse

description: Construction of Yatta municipality slaughter house (Lot 1) which will meet animal welfare and health and safety considerations. The slaughterhouse is planned for the slaughter of up to 200 small ruminants, 25 cattle, and 1 camel per day during 316 workdays per year. Works will include the construction of the slaughter facility, equipping of the slaughter house, and construction of a water treatment facility. As Samua Breeding Centre (Lot 2) is being developed to serve as a “one-stop” centre for all matters regarding animal breeding and genetic improvement. The works include construction of a laboratory block and yard improvements. Both will support the development of the livestock sector in West Bank, Palestine.
title: Construction of: Lot 1- As Samua breed station including laboratory building and supplying and installing surveillance system and Lot 2: Yatta Slaughterhouse
